OL,4,Cdesperate wait for their release
OL,6,FShe continued: "We didn't know
OL,7,Fanything about them for two years. We
OL,8,Fwere so worried about them. We didn't
OL,9,Fknow what they were going through. We
OL,10,Fheard they tortured our hostages; they
OL,11,Fstarved them. We didn't know if they
OL,12,Fwere alive. You know, every day they
OL,13,Fcan just decide to shoot"
OL,15,FThat knowledge has been agonising. For
OL,16,Fyears, Gali and Ziv were in and out of
OL,17,Fher house every day, playing on the
OL,18,Fsame football team as her son, sharing
OL,19,Fbirthday parties on the Kibbutz every
OL,20,Fyear.
OL,26,@uD@YO]
